  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"aphelios","win":["Aphelios","Aphelios","Aphelios","Aphelios","Aphelios","Skill","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Aphelios owns this window: with Severum/Gravitum or Calibrum's long-range Q marking you, he out-ranges and out-DPSs your melee-range Silver Bolts, so respect his gun rotations and never walk up while his lifesteal or slow chamber is loaded."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Aphelios' Moonlight Vigil is a huge burst-and-clear ult that comes online while your Final Hour is still a duel tool that needs three W stacks to matter; a good Aphelios plus support all-in beats a naked Vayne 6, so only commit Condemn-into-wall if you have your own CC to chain."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even. Your first item plus tumble-resets start making Silver Bolts and invisibility pay off, but Aphelios' first-item spike on his damage guns keeps him a real threat, so trade cooldown-for-cooldown rather than raw autos."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vayne takes over: %HP true damage from Silver Bolts, Final Hour stealth in the tumble, and Condemn peel let you kite Aphelios, who has no dash or escape once you close distance in a teamfight."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach items and three-stack Silver Bolts before he bursts you","A support with hard CC to guarantee your all-in","Sidestep Calibrum marks and punish his weak-gun windows"],"foe":["Keep you at max range with Calibrum/Infernum to farm poke","Hit level 6 with Gravitum slow to land Moonlight Vigil","Fight early before your true damage and stealth scale"]},"early":"Aphelios out-ranges you at 1-2 with whatever gun pair he opens; last-hit from behind the caster minions, never contest a CS he can body-block, and expect to concede lane pressure while you farm safely.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay his: his gun rotation out-trades your short range and his 6 spikes harder than yours, so farm, dodge marks, and only fight when your support lands CC first.","late":"Once your first item and stacks land it evens out and then flips hard for you; kite with Tumble, use Condemn to peel his all-in, and pop Final Hour in extended fights where he can't escape your true damage.","whys":["Aphelios out-ranges and out-DPSs melee-range Vayne at level 1.","At 2 his loaded gun chamber still out-trades your short-range autos.","Level 3 Aphelios' gun rotation punishes every step you take forward.","Through 4-5 his damage guns keep you pinned off CS.","His level 6 Moonlight Vigil bursts harder than a stack-hungry Final Hour.","By one item you've closed the gap and trade evenly cooldown-for-cooldown.","With two-plus items Vayne's %HP true damage and stealth kite an escape-less Aphelios."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"ashe","win":["Ashe","Ashe","Ashe","Ashe","Ashe","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ashe dominates early: her Frost Shot permaslow means every auto chips you and kites you out of your own trading range, and Volley zones the wave so you can't step up for Silver Bolts stacks without eating a slow-plus-poke chunk."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ashe's Enchanted Crystal Arrow is a global game-ender that lets her support all-in you from fog, while your Final Hour at 6 still needs three W stacks to convert; a landed R stun on you usually means you die before Condemn matters."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The lane flips to you. Once your first item lands, Tumble-resets let you stack Silver Bolts through her slow, and you can Condemn her when she has no dash to escape the all-in."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vayne wins hard: %HP true damage shreds Ashe's low-HP frame, Final Hour stealth breaks her R follow-up, and she is one of the most immobile carries to kite in a 5v5."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the slow-poke phase and reach your first item","Stack Silver Bolts through Frost Shot with Tumble resets","Bait or dodge her Crystal Arrow before all-inning"],"foe":["Permaslow you with Frost Shot to deny CS and stacks","Land Enchanted Crystal Arrow to set up a support all-in","Zone the wave with Volley so you never trade up"]},"early":"Ashe's Frost Shot permaslow and Volley poke shove you off the wave; last-hit patiently from behind minions, buy early sustain, and accept you lose the level 1-2 trade to her constant slow.","mid":"Through 3-6 she keeps the lead with slows and her global R all-in; don't facecheck fog, respect her level 6 pick threat, and just farm until your first item comes online.","late":"After your first item it swings to you and stays there; kite her with Tumble, Condemn her flat since she has no dash, and Final Hour true damage melts her fragile immobile frame in every teamfight.","whys":["Ashe's Frost Shot slow chips and kites you from level 1.","At 2 Volley plus slow zones you off the wave and out-trades you.","Level 3 her permaslow keeps you out of Silver Bolts range.","Through 4-5 constant slow-poke denies your CS and stacks.","Her level 6 global Crystal Arrow enables a lethal support all-in.","By your first item Tumble resets let you stack through her slow and take over.","With two-plus items Vayne's true damage and stealth shred an immobile Ashe."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"caitlyn","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Pure skill matchup that leans on your discipline: Caitlyn out-ranges you massively and will trap-plus-Q poke, so the phase is even only if you refuse her bait, last-hit from max range, and never step onto a Yordle Snap Trap for a Headshot combo."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Neither ult swings the duel: Caitlyn's Ace in the Hole is a peel-check not a burst, and your Final Hour needs stacks. It stays even, decided by whether you dodge her traps and net-reset while she avoids feeding your Silver Bolts."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even. Caitlyn's first item keeps her lane-bully poke while your Tumble-reset stacking starts closing the range gap; whoever plays their cooldowns and support CC cleaner wins the trade."},{"when":"Late","text":"Flips slightly your way but still skill-dependent: if you reach Caitlyn past her net you kill her instantly with true damage, but a good Caitlyn kites you with 90 Caliber Net and Traps, so it comes down to your engage angle."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Snap Traps and net so you can close range","Farm safely to items where your true damage takes over","Punish her when 90 Caliber Net is on cooldown"],"foe":["Zone you with traps and headshot poke at max range","Keep 90 Caliber Net up to kite your all-in","Deny your Silver Bolts stacks with superior range"]},"early":"A skill-decided lane: Caitlyn out-ranges you and threatens Trap-into-Headshot combos, so last-hit from behind minions, never walk onto a trap, and take only free autos when she uses Q on the wave.","mid":"Still even through 6; respect her poke and Ace in the Hole, dodge net, and farm toward the items where Vayne's %HP true damage starts to outscale her lane-bully phase.","late":"It's your discipline versus her kite: land a Condemn or support CC past her 90 Caliber Net and true damage deletes her, but let her net you first and she resets the fight, so pick your engage angle carefully.","whys":["Caitlyn out-ranges you but even play trades neutral at level 1.","At 2 it stays skill-based on whether you dodge her Q poke.","Level 3 traps threaten you but disciplined spacing keeps it even.","Through 4-5 clean CS and trap-dodging hold the lane neutral.","Neither ult breaks the even duel at level 6.","By one item your closing power offsets her poke for an even trade.","With items it stays skill-decided on whether you beat her net kite."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"corki","win":["Corki","Corki","Corki","Corki","Corki","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Corki bullies you early: Phosphorus Bomb plus Gatling Gun shred and his Valkyrie mobility mean he pokes from range you can't answer, so concede the trade phase and farm from behind minions while he burns mana on poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Corki's Missile Barrage adds waveclear and long-range chip that pressures you off the wave, while your Final Hour still needs three Silver Bolts stacks to duel; his 6 out-values yours, so don't all-in without support CC to lock him."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The matchup swings to you as his poke falls off relative to your scaling; once you hit your first item, Tumble-reset stacking through his damage starts winning extended trades."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vayne takes over hard, reflected in the 56.76% win rate: %HP true damage ignores his squishy build, Final Hour stealth dodges his Valkyrie escape, and you kite him down once you're on top of him."}],"wants":{"you":["Weather his early poke and reach your first item","Stack Silver Bolts in extended fights, not short pokes","All-in with support CC before he Valkyries away"],"foe":["Poke you down with Phosphorus Bomb and Gatling Gun","Use Valkyrie mobility to trade and disengage safely","Fight early before your true-damage scaling comes online"]},"early":"Corki out-pokes you at 1-2 with Phosphorus Bomb and superior range; last-hit safely, dodge his skillshot bomb, and don't try to trade autos into his Gatling Gun zone.","mid":"He keeps the lead through 6 with poke and Missile Barrage waveclear; farm patiently, respect his Missile Barrage chip, and wait for your first item before contesting fights.","late":"From your first item on it's firmly your matchup; kite with Tumble, chase him past his Valkyrie with Condemn range, and let Final Hour true damage melt his squishy frame in every skirmish.","whys":["Corki's early poke out-trades melee-range Vayne at level 1.","At 2 Phosphorus Bomb plus autos chunk you before you can answer.","Level 3 Gatling Gun and range keep you off the wave.","Through 4-5 his poke and mobility deny your CS and stacks.","His level 6 Missile Barrage out-values a stack-hungry Final Hour.","By one item your scaling flips the extended trades to you.","With two-plus items Vayne's true damage shreds squishy, escape-reliant Corki."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"draven","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"A coinflip skill lane at exactly 50%: Draven's Spinning Axe autos hit like a truck and Blood Rush lets him chase, but every axe he catches pulls him out of position, so the phase is even and decided by whether you punish his catches or eat his all-in."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Neither ult dominates: Draven's Whirling Death is execute pressure but no engage, and your Final Hour needs stacks; it stays even, hinging on whether he snowballs his axes off a kill or you survive to farm."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even. Draven's first-item axe damage is terrifying, but your Tumble-reset stacking and Condemn peel start matching it; whoever plays the cooldown windows and support CC better takes the trade."},{"when":"Late","text":"Skill-decided still: if Draven is even he out-damages you, but %HP true damage and Condemn let you kite and interrupt his axe-catch rhythm, so a clean kite flips it while a fed Draven runs you down."}],"wants":{"you":["Punish him when he chases axes out of position","Survive his snowball and reach your true-damage items","Condemn to interrupt his axe-catch and Blood Rush chase"],"foe":["Land Spinning Axe autos to win every short trade","Snowball early kills into an unstoppable axe lead","Catch axes safely and all-in with Stand Aside CC"]},"early":"A pure coinflip: Draven's Spinning Axes out-damage your autos, but chasing them drags him off position; last-hit clean, punish greedy catches, and don't facecheck his all-in without your support ready.","mid":"Stays even through 6; respect his damage and Whirling Death execute, farm your stacks, and look to trade when his axes drop or his Blood Rush is down.","late":"It comes down to your kite versus his snowball; if even, Condemn and Final Hour true damage let you interrupt his axe rhythm and melt him, but a fed Draven will run you down, so space carefully.","whys":["Draven's axes out-hit you but his catches even the level 1 trade.","At 2 it stays coinflip on whether you punish his positioning.","Level 3 his damage is scary but greedy catches keep it even.","Through 4-5 clean farming and punishing catches hold it neutral.","Neither ult breaks the even duel at level 6.","By one item your peel and scaling match his axe damage evenly.","With items it stays skill-decided between your kite and his snowball."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"ezreal","win":["Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ezreal pokes you out early: Mystic Shot with Manaflow harass chips you every time you step for CS, and his E Arcane Shift means you can never punish him even when he's out of position, so concede the poke phase and farm safely."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ezreal's Trueshot Barrage adds long-range chip and reset pressure while your Final Hour is still a stack-hungry duel tool; he out-values the level 6 timer, so avoid all-ins unless your support can lock his Arcane Shift."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Lane swings to you: once your first item lands, Tumble-reset Silver Bolts stacking overtakes his poke, and if you Condemn or CC him after his E is down he simply dies."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vayne wins decisively, matching the 55.98% win rate: %HP true damage shreds his squishy build, Final Hour stealth negates his skillshot poke, and once his single Arcane Shift is burned he has no way to escape your kite."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Mystic Shot and reach your first-item spike","Catch him after Arcane Shift is on cooldown","Stack Silver Bolts in extended fights past his poke"],"foe":["Poke you with Mystic Shot and Essence Flux from range","Use Arcane Shift to dodge your Condemn and all-ins","Farm safe with W-empowered pushes and Trueshot chip"]},"early":"Ezreal harasses you with Mystic Shot every time you go for CS and Arcane Shift keeps him untouchable; last-hit from behind minions, dodge his skillshots, and don't try to trade into his poke.","mid":"He keeps the edge through 6 with poke and Trueshot Barrage; farm patiently, respect his safety, and wait for your first item rather than forcing a losing all-in.","late":"From your first item on it's firmly yours; bait his Arcane Shift, Condemn him when it's down, and let Final Hour true damage melt his squishy frame while stealth eats his poke.","whys":["Ezreal's Mystic Shot poke out-harasses melee-range Vayne at level 1.","At 2 his range plus Manaflow harass keeps chipping you off CS.","Level 3 Arcane Shift means you can't punish his poke.","Through 4-5 constant skillshot poke denies your stacks and CS.","His level 6 Trueshot Barrage out-values a stack-hungry Final Hour.","By one item your reset stacking overtakes his falling-off poke.","With two-plus items Vayne's true damage shreds an escape-spent Ezreal."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"heimerdinger","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once Heimerdinger fills the lane with three H-28G Evolution Turrets you lose the free CS and the ability to walk up, so Tumble through minions to auto him only when his turrets are on cooldown or you'll eat concentrated beam damage and a W rocket poke. Ask your support to body-block or dive a turret so you can Q past the wall and force a real trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His CH-3X Lightning Grenade point-blank stun plus turret focus is a genuine all-in threat, and Final Hour does not save you from being rooted in the turret field. Pop R for the movement speed and extra invisibility on Tumble to reposition out of the grenade cone rather than to commit a kill you can't finish through his zone."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After your first item you can start clearing a turret in a couple of Silver Bolts procs, but he simply drops another with W's passive charges, so this phase still belongs to his zoning. Trade only when a turret expires and hold your Condemn for his engage support, not to waste it on empty space."},{"when":"Late","text":"With two-plus items and Final Hour up you finally out-scale him: Silver Bolts shreds his squishy body and turrets in true-damage ticks, and you can flank the teamfight so his stationary turret wall and slow grenade never line up on you. Kite along the edge, let him commit W and E, then dive the backline once his zone is spent."}],"wants":{"you":["Turrets on cooldown so you can Tumble in for a clean trade","A support that can dive or soak the turret field for you","Late-game side angles where his stationary zone can't cover you"],"foe":["A full three-turret wall funneling you into beam range","Landing the CH-3X Lightning Grenade stun to chain turret focus","A slow, grindy lane where his poke out-values your all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are close: neither of you wants to commit before turrets and Silver Bolts stacks come online, so farm safe and last-hit from max range while respecting his W rocket poke.","mid":"From 3 through 6 Heimerdinger takes over — his turret wall denies your CS and walk-ups, and the CH-3X grenade turns any greedy Tumble into a stun-and-focus death, so play for scaling not kills.","late":"Once you finish your first item and beyond, his zone keeps you honest until two items, then Final Hour plus true-damage Silver Bolts lets you clear turrets fast and flank around his static setup.","whys":["Level 1 is even because both champs poke and farm without a real all-in threat.","Level 2 stays a skill matchup as neither of you has the tools to force a decisive trade yet.","Level 3 is still even before his full turret field and your Silver Bolts online.","At Levels 4-5 Heimerdinger's three-turret wall zones your CS and walk-ups, favouring him.","At Level 6 his grenade stun plus turret focus is a stronger all-in than your Final Hour can answer.","At first item he simply replaces cleared turrets, so his zone still out-values your trades.","By two-plus items Final Hour and true-damage Silver Bolts let Vayne shred him and flank his static zone."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"jhin","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Jhin","Jhin","Skill","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jhin's Deadly Flourish root off a Dancing Grenade or minion-hop slow is his whole trading pattern, so never Tumble straight at him in a line where he can W-root you into a fourth-shot crit. Weave Silver Bolts stacks on him during his long reload windows, and use your support's minion wave to break his line of sight before he can confirm the root."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Curtain Call gives him global pressure and executes you from screen-away if you're low, and this is a window Vayne can't contest since Final Hour doesn't stop the missiles. Respect his ult range when you're under half health, hold Condemn to cancel his channel if he's close, and don't over-extend for CS during his level-6 timer."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This phase is even again: your first item gives you a Silver Bolts kill threat but he spikes hard on crit items and his fourth shot plus W still punishes bad spacing. Trade in short Tumble-auto bursts when his fourth shot is spent and disengage before he reloads and re-roots."},{"when":"Late","text":"With two-plus items and Final Hour, Vayne pulls ahead — Silver Bolts melts his immobile, crit-reliant body and you can close the gap his kit hates. Kite onto him after he burns his fourth shot and W, use Condemn to peel his backline, and force the fight in tight spaces where he can't safely poke or ult."}],"wants":{"you":["His fourth shot and Deadly Flourish on cooldown before you commit","Minions and support to break his root line of sight","Late-game close-range fights where his immobility loses"],"foe":["A clean Deadly Flourish root to land a fourth-shot crit","Curtain Call picks on you when you're low or over-extended","Long lanes where he pokes and reloads at max range"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are even: both farm and poke at range, and neither can hard-commit before Jhin's root setup or your Silver Bolts stacks are reliable.","mid":"At 4 through 5 Jhin edges ahead — his Deadly Flourish root into fourth-shot crit and his Curtain Call at 6 give him more kill pressure than Vayne can create through minions.","late":"First item is even as your kill threat comes online, then by two-plus items Final Hour and true-damage Silver Bolts let Vayne shred his immobile crit body and win close fights.","whys":["Level 1 is even as both poke and farm without a committal threat.","Level 2 stays a skill lane before Jhin's root combos or your stacks come online.","Level 3 remains even with neither champ holding a decisive all-in.","At Levels 4-5 Jhin's Deadly Flourish root into a fourth-shot crit gives him the trading edge.","At Level 6 Curtain Call adds long-range execute pressure Vayne can't answer.","At first item the lane evens out as Vayne's Silver Bolts kill threat matches Jhin's crit spike.","By two-plus items Final Hour and Silver Bolts let Vayne melt Jhin's immobile body up close."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"jinx","win":["Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jinx out-ranges you hard with Fishbones rockets and her Pow-Pow attack-speed ramp, so every time you walk up to last-hit she chunks you for free from beyond auto range. Don't try to Tumble-trade into her — farm from max distance, respect her W Zap slow that sets up her jungler, and only commit when her rockets and Zap are down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Super Mega Death Rocket gives her a global finisher and huge waveclear, and combined with Excited passive movement she snowballs any kill instantly. Final Hour helps you dodge her R with Tumble stealth-repositioning, but you can't all-in her through minions, so use 6 to reposition and farm safe rather than to force a fight you're behind in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The lane starts to even here — your first item plus Silver Bolts gives you a real kill threat if you can close the gap, while she's still fragile and immobile. Look for support engage or a flank so you get onto her after she's committed rockets, then burst her before she resets Excited to run."},{"when":"Late","text":"By two-plus items it's a coin-flip skill duel: Silver Bolts shreds her non-existent mobility, but she deletes you first if you mispace into her rockets and crit auto-resets. Win by kiting in from angles she can't rocket, forcing her to burn Zap and Flame Chompers on your support, then diving her the instant her escape tools are spent."}],"wants":{"you":["Her rockets and Zap slow on cooldown before you engage","Support engage or a flank to close her range gap","Tight fights where her lack of mobility lets Silver Bolts finish"],"foe":["Free rocket poke while you walk up to farm","Landing Zap or Flame Chompers to set up a kill","An open lane where she ramps Pow-Pow and out-ranges you"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Jinx — her Fishbones range and Pow-Pow attack-speed ramp poke you off every CS, and her Zap slow sets up ganks before your Silver Bolts kill threat exists.","mid":"Around level 6 the lane evens: her Super Mega Death Rocket is scary but you can Tumble-dodge it, and your first item finally gives you the burst to punish her if she over-commits.","late":"From first item on it's a skill duel — Silver Bolts melts her immobile body, but a single missed dodge into her rockets and crit resets deletes you first.","whys":["At Level 1 Jinx's range and Pow-Pow ramp poke Vayne off the wave.","At Level 2 her rocket poke and attack-speed lead keep the trading edge.","At Level 3 she still out-ranges and out-damages a stack-less Vayne.","At Levels 4-5 her Zap setup and sustained poke keep the lane in her favour.","At Level 6 the lane evens as Vayne can Tumble-dodge the rocket and threaten back with first-item burst.","At first item it stays even — Vayne's kill threat matches Jinx's fragile, immobile spike.","By two-plus items it's a skill coin-flip: Silver Bolts shreds her but her rockets delete a mispositioned Vayne."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"kaisa","win":["Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Skill","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kai'Sa stacks her passive Plasma with W Icathian Rain and autos, and once she pops the Plasma bonus-damage burst she can two-shot you in a short window. Don't stand next to minions she's already Plasma-marked you through — Tumble out of her W missiles, respect that her E gives her attack speed and invisibility for a surprise trade, and only auto her when her W is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Killer Instinct lets her dash onto or across the map with a shield, so she out-all-ins you if she's evolved W and hits Plasma stacks; Final Hour is your equalizer for the stealth-dodge and the extra Condemn range. Hold E for her R dash-in — a well-timed Condemn cancels her all-in and can wall her for a kill if your support follows up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is her strongest relative window: evolved Q or W plus a completed item lets her burst you before Silver Bolts ramps, so play respectful. Trade in short bursts when her W and E are down, keep minions between you and her Plasma marks, and don't duel her straight up until your second item is close."},{"when":"Late","text":"By two-plus items with Final Hour, Vayne flips it — true-damage Silver Bolts shreds her building HP and Condemn hard-counters her R dash by stunning her into a wall. Kite her E engage, save Condemn for her all-in, and force the fight after she's used Killer Instinct so she has no reset to escape your three-stack execute."}],"wants":{"you":["Her W and E on cooldown before you auto-trade","Condemn saved to wall her Killer Instinct dash","Late-game duels where Silver Bolts out-scales her HP"],"foe":["Full Plasma stacks to burst you in her short window","An evolved W or E first-item spike to out-trade you","Killer Instinct resets to all-in and escape freely"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 favour Kai'Sa — her Plasma-stack burst, W poke, and E attack-speed steroid let her out-trade Vayne before Silver Bolts ramps, so farm safe and dodge her missiles.","mid":"At level 6 her Killer Instinct all-in is strong, but this phase evens out because Final Hour and a saved Condemn let you cancel her dash and punish her engage.","late":"From first item she still spikes on evolutions, then by two-plus items true-damage Silver Bolts and a wall-Condemn on her R flip the matchup firmly to Vayne.","whys":["At Level 1 Kai'Sa's Plasma poke and range edge favour her.","At Level 2 her W and passive stacking give her the trading lead.","At Level 3 her burst window out-damages a stack-less Vayne.","At Levels 4-5 her evolutions and E steroid keep her ahead in trades.","At Level 6 Killer Instinct gives her a stronger all-in than Vayne can answer early.","At first item the lane evens as Final Hour and a saved Condemn cancel her dash.","By two-plus items Silver Bolts and a wall-Condemn on her R flip it to Vayne."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"kalista","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Kalista","Kalista","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kalista's Pierce spear plus her passive hop lets her kite you endlessly and chunk you while you try to walk up for CS, and Rend stacks make every trade snowball if she gets spears into you. Don't chase her hops — Tumble to close only when her jump is on its animation cooldown, farm from range, and let Silver Bolts stacks build rather than trading auto-for-auto into her superior mobility."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Fate's Call turns her support into a second engage and lets her all-in with pull-and-CC, so respect the level-6 timer even though it's an even phase. Final Hour gives you the movement speed and Condemn range to disengage her spear kiting; save Condemn to stun the support she launches or to peel yourself out of the Rend-stack burst."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kalista spikes here — her Rend execute and spear DPS on a completed item out-trade you before Silver Bolts fully ramps, and her hop makes her hard to pin. Play for scaling: dodge spears with Tumble, don't duel her in the open, and wait for your two-item power before forcing the fight."},{"when":"Late","text":"By two-plus items with Final Hour, Vayne wins the duel — true-damage Silver Bolts shreds her low-HP body faster than her Rend stacks can burst you, and Condemn cancels her Fate's Call engage. Kite in from angles, force her to commit her hop and support launch, then delete her once her mobility reset is spent."}],"wants":{"you":["Her hop on cooldown so you can Tumble in and pin her","Condemn saved for her Fate's Call engage or the launched support","Late-game where Silver Bolts out-DPS her Rend stacks"],"foe":["Free spear poke while you walk up for CS","Rend stacks and first-item DPS to out-trade you","Endless hop-kiting so you can never pin her down"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are an even skill lane: Kalista pokes with spears and kites, but without full Rend stacks or an item she can't hard-commit, so match her CS and dodge Pierce.","mid":"At 5 through 6 Kalista edges ahead — her Rend stack execute, spear DPS, and Fate's Call all-in out-trade Vayne before Silver Bolts ramps.","late":"By two-plus items with Final Hour, true-damage Silver Bolts shreds her fragile body and Condemn cancels her engage, flipping the duel to Vayne.","whys":["Level 1 is even as both poke and farm without a committal threat.","Level 2 stays a skill lane before Rend stacks or items come online.","Level 3 remains even with neither holding a decisive all-in.","Levels 4-5 stay even until her Rend stacks and DPS fully ramp.","At Level 5-6 window her Rend execute and Fate's Call give her the trading edge.","At first item her spear DPS and Rend spike out-trade a still-ramping Vayne.","By two-plus items Silver Bolts and a Condemn on Fate's Call flip the duel to Vayne."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"karthus","win":["Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Karthus bot spams Lay Waste — a delayed AoE burst that hits harder on isolated targets — so standing to last-hit means eating repeated Q damage you can't dodge if you're greedy for CS. Tumble sideways through his Q cast to break the target circle, farm from behind your minions, and don't try to auto-trade into his Wall slow that sets up his poke and jungler."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Requiem is a global execute that snowballs the whole map and can finish you from anywhere if you're low, so respect his ult when your health dips and buy sustain. Final Hour lets you Tumble-dodge his Lay Waste more reliably, but you can't all-in through his Wall and range, so use 6 to reposition and farm rather than force a losing fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His mana and AP spike lets Karthus zone the whole lane with Q spam plus E Defile burn, keeping you off CS while he scales, so this phase is still his. Only walk up when his Q is on cooldown, keep minions between you to prevent isolated Lay Waste crits, and grind toward your two-item power."},{"when":"Late","text":"By two-plus items with Final Hour, Vayne finally out-scales — true-damage Silver Bolts melts his squishy, immobile body if you can close, and Condemn stuns him out of a Wall or channel. Flank around his Q zone, force the fight after he burns Wall, and burst him before Requiem or his support can peel you off."}],"wants":{"you":["His Lay Waste on cooldown before you walk up to trade","Minions between you to avoid isolated Q bursts","Late-game flanks to close on his immobile body"],"foe":["Free Lay Waste poke while you farm","Wall slow to zone you and set up his poke","Requiem execute picks when you're low across the map"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 favour Karthus — Lay Waste spam pokes you off CS and his Wall slow zones your walk-ups before Silver Bolts stacks matter, so farm safe and dodge his Q.","mid":"From 4 through 6 he keeps control — his mana spike, Defile burn, and global Requiem execute out-pressure Vayne, who can't all-in through his range and Wall.","late":"His first item still zones you, then by two-plus items Final Hour and true-damage Silver Bolts let Vayne flank and melt his immobile body to flip the matchup.","whys":["At Level 1 Karthus's Lay Waste poke controls the lane over a stack-less Vayne.","At Level 2 his Q spam and Wall setup keep the trading edge.","At Level 3 his poke still zones Vayne off farm.","At Levels 4-5 his mana and Defile burn keep the lane in his favour.","At Level 6 Requiem's global execute adds pressure Vayne can't match.","At first item his AP spike lets him zone the whole lane with Q and burn.","By two-plus items Final Hour and Silver Bolts let Vayne flank and melt his immobile body."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"kogmaw","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Vayne","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Neither of you wants to fight early: Kog'Maw is a scaling immobile hyper-carry and you are a scaling duelist, so the 3-5 window is a farm race where whoever's support lands CC decides it. Use Tumble to dodge his W-empowered autos and only commit Silver Bolts when his support has burned engage."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Final Hour flips this window your way: the stealth from Tumble during ult plus the movement speed lets you dodge his Bio-Arcane Barrage autos and Living Artillery and close the gap he needs to kite. Kog'Maw has no dash, so a support engage under your R is a near-guaranteed kill before he can pass 3 stacks."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kog'Maw's first item (Nashor's or Guinsoo's route) gives him massive DPS if allowed to free-fire, so this is genuinely even at one item; your job is to not let him stand still. His %HP-max W shreds your low HP pool if you facecheck, so respect his range."},{"when":"Late","text":"At 2+ items Kog'Maw out-DPSes almost everyone from max range with W and R poke, and a peeled Kog'Maw beats a Vayne who can't reach him. If his team walls you off, you lose the sustained trade, so you must flank or use E-Condemn a peeler to actually touch him."}],"wants":{"you":["A support with hard engage (Leona/Naut) to pin the immobile Kog'Maw","Reaching him during Final Hour stealth before he stacks W","Isolating him from his peel so you can Silver Bolts his low HP"],"foe":["A pocket peel/enchanter support keeping you off him","Free-firing from max range with Bio-Arcane Barrage stacks","A frontline that walls you out of his auto range"]},"early":"Level 1-2 is a pure farm standoff: Kog'Maw wants to hit level 6 and items untouched, you want to scale safely, so play behind minions and only trade autos when his support is out of CC range.","mid":"Through 3-6 it stays skill-dependent; abuse Tumble to weave last-hits and dodge his empowered W autos, but don't dive his %max-HP damage without your support's CC committed first.","late":"Once Final Hour is up you spike hardest in the duel because stealth and MS let you chase the dashless Kog'Maw down, but at 2+ items a peeled Kog'Maw's max-range W and R DPS reclaims the neutral if you can't reach him.","whys":["Level 1 is a mutual scaling farm lane where neither ADC has a kill pattern.","Level 2 stays even as both of you prioritize CS over a risky first trade.","Level 3 is skill-based since your Tumble kiting and his W poke roughly cancel out.","Levels 4-5 remain a coin-flip decided by support CC, not ADC strength.","Level 6 is even because his Living Artillery and your Final Hour arrive together with no clear duel winner yet.","First item favors you: Final Hour's stealth and MS let you close on and burst the immobile Kog'Maw before he ramps.","At 2+ items it swings back to skill as a peeled Kog'Maw's max-range W and R DPS offsets your dive threat."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"lucian","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Lucian","Lucian","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lucian's lane bully pattern (Piercing Light Q, passive double-tap, Relentless Pursuit E dash) lets him win short trades, but he can't hard-commit while you have Tumble to reposition and Condemn to punish his dash-in. Play this even by farming behind minions and only Silver-Bolt-trading when his E is down; if he burns Relentless Pursuit aggressively, walk him into a Condemn stun."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Lucian's Culling arrives and, paired with his E resets on trade hits, this is his strongest window against your squishy frame. Your Final Hour helps you kite, but a Lucian who dashes in, unloads The Culling, and E-resets out can chunk you before you stack Silver Bolts, so don't greed extended fights here."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Lucian spikes hard at one item (Essence Reaver/Navori) where his dash-weave-Culling combo is at peak burst and mobility, and you are still a two-to-three-item champion. Respect his all-in range and use Condemn purely defensively to interrupt his E engage rather than fishing for wall stuns."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is where you take over: at 2+ items Silver Bolts and Final Hour turn Lucian's short range and low HP against him, and his lane-bully burst falls off relative to your true-damage DPS. Kite with Tumble, save Condemn to cancel his Relentless Pursuit escape, and you out-duel him in extended trades and teamfights."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching 2+ items where Silver Bolts shreds his low HP","Saving Condemn to interrupt his Relentless Pursuit dash","Extended trades once Final Hour lets you kite his burst"],"foe":["Winning short trades with his Q double-tap and E resets","His level 6 Culling all-in before you have items","Snowballing the early lead his mobility gives him"]},"early":"Level 1-3 is skill-based: Lucian's passive double-tap and Piercing Light out-poke a raw auto trade, but Tumble lets you dodge and reset, so farm even and don't eat free Q-passive combos.","mid":"From 4 through 6 Lucian pulls ahead as his Culling and Relentless Pursuit resets give him a burst-and-escape all-in your squishy early frame can't match; play safe and hold Condemn to punish his engage dash.","late":"Once you hit 2+ items you flip the matchup hard, because Silver Bolts' true damage and Final Hour let you kite his short range and out-DPS his frontloaded burst.","whys":["Level 1 is even; Lucian's poke is offset by your Tumble mobility in a farm lane.","Level 2 stays skill-based as neither of you has a committal all-in yet.","Level 3 is a coin-flip decided by whether you dodge his Q-passive trades.","Levels 4-5 remain even, with his trade wins balanced by your Condemn punish threat.","Level 6 favors Lucian because The Culling plus E resets give him a burst all-in you can't yet answer.","First item favors Lucian as his Essence Reaver dash-weave combo peaks before your scaling comes online.","At 2+ items you win: Silver Bolts and Final Hour out-DPS his short-range burst that has fallen off."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"missfortune","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Miss Fortune's lane is all about Double Up (Q) bounce poke and passive Love Tap movement-speed autos, so she chips you whenever you step to CS. Use Tumble to break line of sight so her Q can't bounce off a minion onto you, and never stand behind a low minion she can execute-bounce through; trade back only when her Q is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Bullet Time is the whole reason this lane is scary: with a support engage or a hook, MF's channel can delete you and your support before you kite out. Keep Final Hour and Tumble ready to break the channel's line, position so a frontline minion wave eats the cone, and never facecheck brush at 6 without vision."},{"when":"1st item","text":"MF spikes hardest around one item with her poke lane snowballing and Bullet Time threatening every fight, while your single-item Vayne is still fragile. Play for CS, dodge Double Up angles, and treat every all-in as lethal if her ult is up plus support CC; don't fight into that."},{"when":"Late","text":"The game inverts at 2+ items: MF has no escape and no reliable self-peel, so once Silver Bolts and Final Hour are online you Tumble onto her, stack true damage, and Condemn her away from her team. In teamfights flank to force her ult early or eat it behind frontline, then clean up."}],"wants":{"you":["Scaling to 2+ items where you out-duel her escape-less kit","Breaking Double Up line-of-sight with Tumble","Flanking or baiting Bullet Time before committing"],"foe":["Poking you down with Double Up and Love Tap autos","Landing a full Bullet Time with support CC or a hook","Snowballing her one-item poke lead before you scale"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are skill-based: MF's Double Up poke punishes sloppy CS, but if you Tumble to break minion bounce lines and only trade on her Q cooldown, you farm even.","mid":"Through 4-6 she edges ahead as Bullet Time plus her poke threaten a lane-ending all-in your squishy frame can't survive; respect the channel and keep Tumble to break its line of sight.","late":"At 2+ items you take over hard because MF has no dash or self-peel, so Final Hour and Silver Bolts let you dive her, stack true damage, and Condemn her out of position.","whys":["Level 1 is even in a farm-and-poke standoff with no all-in yet.","Level 2 stays skill-based as her Q poke is offset by your Tumble dodging.","Level 3 remains a coin-flip decided by whether you break her Double Up angles.","Levels 4-5 stay even, with her poke balanced against your safe-scaling potential.","Level 6 favors Miss Fortune because Bullet Time plus support CC is a lane-ending all-in you can't yet answer.","First item favors MF as her poke lead and ult threat peak before your scaling arrives.","At 2+ items you win: the escape-less MF gets run down by Final Hour, Silver Bolts, and Condemn."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"nilah","win":["Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Nilah is a melee lane bully with absurd early sustain: her passive doubles healing, Slipstream (W) gives dodge frames plus lifesteal, and Jubilant Veil negates a full auto and reduces AoE. When she dashes in with Q's extended range you can't win the raw trade, so Condemn her the instant she commits and Tumble away rather than dueling her sustain."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Apotheosis lets Nilah pull your whole side into a fight and buff her support, and her W dodge makes her frustrating to burst even with Final Hour up. Your ult helps you kite, but a Nilah all-in with support CC still beats you here, so use Condemn to peel her off and disengage instead of standing to trade."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Nilah's Immortal Shieldbow/Bloodthirster spike makes her lane-dominant sustain even harder to out-trade at one item, and she'll look to run you down. Keep spacing with Tumble, bait her Jubilant Veil before you commit Silver Bolts, and never fight into her W dodge frames or you waste your whole combo."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is your only clear window: at 2+ items Silver Bolts' %max-HP true damage finally out-paces her healing and Final Hour lets you kite her short melee range. Save Condemn to interrupt her Slipstream engage, stack Bolts from max distance, and in teamfights position so her Apotheosis pull can't chain you before you're ramped."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching 2+ items where Silver Bolts out-damages her sustain","Saving Condemn to peel her Slipstream engage","Kiting her short melee range with Final Hour and Tumble"],"foe":["Winning every early trade with her sustain and dodge frames","Bursting you inside her Jubilant Veil damage reduction","All-in with Apotheosis pull plus support CC before you scale"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Nilah: her doubled healing and Slipstream lifesteal win any melee-range exchange, so give ground, farm at max range, and Condemn her the moment she dashes in.","mid":"Through 3-6 she stays ahead because Jubilant Veil eats your autos and Apotheosis threatens an all-in you can't survive; hold Condemn defensively and refuse to trade into her dodge and sustain.","late":"At 2+ items you finally flip it, as Silver Bolts' true damage overwhelms her lifesteal and Final Hour lets you kite the short-range Nilah down while Condemn peels her engage.","whys":["Level 1 favors Nilah; her doubled healing and lifesteal win the melee trade outright.","Level 2 stays Nilah's as Slipstream dodge frames let her trade for free.","Level 3 is hers because Jubilant Veil negates your autos in every exchange.","Levels 4-5 remain Nilah-favored with her sustain still out-trading your fragile frame.","Level 6 favors Nilah since Apotheosis plus support CC is an all-in you can't yet survive.","First item stays Nilah's as her Shieldbow/Bloodthirster sustain spike out-trades your single item.","At 2+ items you win: Silver Bolts' true damage finally out-paces her healing and you kite her melee range."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"samira","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Samira","Samira","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Samira wants melee-range brawls: her passive builds a style rank, Flair (Q) pokes at range while her dash (E) closes and Blade Whirl (W) shreds your autos and projectiles. Keep her at max range with Tumble, never let her stack S-rank on you, and Condemn her the moment she E-dashes in so she can't chain her combo."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Inferno Trigger is a reset-fueled AoE ult that can 100-to-0 you if she reaches melee with support CC; her W also blocks your Condemn projectile mid-cast. This is her strongest window, so keep spacing, don't fight into Blade Whirl, and use Final Hour purely to kite out of her dash range rather than trading."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Samira spikes hugely at one item (Immortal Shieldbow) where her all-in becomes lethal and her lifesteal sustains her through trades. Play for CS behind minions, deny her the E-dash gap-close by hugging your tower, and never let her get a reset chain going with a support engage."},{"when":"Late","text":"You take over at 2+ items: Samira must be in melee to do damage, so Silver Bolts' true damage and Final Hour let you kite her and Condemn her out of every all-in. In teamfights bait her Blade Whirl, then stack Bolts from range and peel her dash so she never lands the reset she needs."}],"wants":{"you":["Scaling to 2+ items where you kite her melee all-in","Saving Condemn to interrupt her E-dash engage","Baiting Blade Whirl before committing Silver Bolts"],"foe":["Reaching melee to stack style and E-reset chains","A full Inferno Trigger with support CC before you scale","Blocking your autos and Condemn with Blade Whirl"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are skill-based: Samira's Flair pokes but she needs melee to snowball, so if you Tumble to hold max range and hug minions you farm even and deny her dash gap-closes.","mid":"At 5-6 she pulls ahead as Immortal Shieldbow and Inferno Trigger make her all-in lethal, especially with support CC; respect her burst, keep spacing, and hold Condemn to break her E engage.","late":"By 2+ items you flip it, because Samira must be in melee to deal damage and Final Hour plus Silver Bolts let you kite and Condemn her out of every reset-hungry all-in.","whys":["Level 1 is even as neither of you has a committal all-in yet.","Level 2 stays skill-based with her poke offset by your Tumble spacing.","Level 3 remains a coin-flip decided by whether you deny her E-dash range.","Levels 4-5 stay even, her melee threat balanced by your kiting.","Level 6 favors Samira because Inferno Trigger plus support CC is a lethal all-in you can't yet answer.","First item favors Samira as her Shieldbow lifesteal and reset burst peak before your scaling.","At 2+ items you win: the melee-bound Samira gets kited and Condemned by Final Hour and Silver Bolts."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"senna","win":["Senna","Senna","Senna","Senna","Senna","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Senna out-ranges you brutally: Piercing Darkness (Q) pokes and heals through minions, her passive autos crit and slow, and every soul she collects grows her range and AD. When she plays as a poke ADC she chips you every time you step to CS, so Tumble to break her Q line, farm at max range, and never trade autos into her longer range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Dawning Shadow gives Senna a global shield/root ult and Curse of the Black Mist (W) can root you if you get clipped, feeding her lane control. You have no way to close the range gap yet, so use Final Hour only to kite out of her poke, dodge her W root, and avoid extended trades where her Q sustain out-values your autos."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Senna's poke lead peaks around her first item while she snowballs souls, and your one-item Vayne is still fragile against her long-range harass. Focus on CS, dodge W roots, and Condemn her only to punish an over-extension; don't fight into her range, just scale safely to your item spike."},{"when":"Late","text":"The lane inverts once you hit two items: Senna is extremely squishy with no hard escape, so Silver Bolts' true damage and Final Hour let you Tumble the range gap and delete her. Save Condemn to cancel her repositioning, close distance behind minions, and in fights flank the backline Senna who can't survive your sustained DPS."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching 2+ items where you close on her squishy frame","Tumbling the range gap to land Silver Bolts","Punishing overextension or a missed W with Condemn"],"foe":["Poking you out with long-range Piercing Darkness","Snowballing souls for bonus range and AD","Rooting you with Curse of the Black Mist to zone lane"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Senna: her superior range and Q poke-heal harass you off every CS while she stacks souls, so play behind minions, Tumble to break her Q line, and refuse the losing auto trade.","mid":"Through 4-6 she stays ahead as soul stacks grow her range and AD and her W root plus global ult give her lane control you can't answer yet; use Final Hour only to kite her poke and dodge roots.","late":"At 2+ items you take over hard, because the escape-less, squishy Senna gets run down once Silver Bolts' true damage and Final Hour let you Tumble the gap and Condemn her repositioning.","whys":["Level 1 favors Senna as her longer range wins the poke standoff outright.","Level 2 stays Senna's with Piercing Darkness harassing you off CS for free.","Level 3 is hers because her soul-stacking range keeps out-trading your autos.","Levels 4-5 remain Senna-favored as her poke and W root zone you out of lane.","Level 6 favors Senna since her global ult and root control outclass your kit before you scale.","First item favors you: at one Vayne item you begin closing the gap and Silver Bolts threatens her squishy frame.","At 2+ items you win outright, running down the escape-less Senna with Final Hour, Silver Bolts, and Condemn."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"seraphine","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Seraphine","Seraphine","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once Seraphine puts a point in her E (Beat Drop) root and pairs it with her enchanter support, standing still to last-hit under threat gets punished hard; take your CS on the move, tumble through her Q (High Note) poke lines, and never walk up in a straight line where she can chain root into her partner's follow-up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Encore (R) is a lane-warping charm that will lock you in place and let their bot lane collapse for a kill; respect it around your level-6 timing and hold your E (Condemn) as a spacing tool, but understand that in the 2v2 her ult plus a support engage still out-threatens your solo all-in here."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item flips the fight the moment you finish it: with Silver Bolts (W) proccing on Seraphine's low base health you shred her far faster than her shields and Q poke can trade back, so start hunting kill windows the instant your Q resets and W is up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, Vayne is the hyper-carry and Seraphine is a low-mobility utility caster with no way to peel your Q-repositioning; kite through her Encore, stay behind your frontline, and clean up teamfights while she can only shield and hope."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 2 items where Silver Bolts melts her squishy base stats","Dodge Beat Drop roots by tumbling instead of standing to CS","Force late 2v2 skirmishes once your Q/W spike online"],"foe":["Land Beat Drop (E) roots to set up her support's engage","Poke you down with High Note (Q) while you farm","Hit Encore (R) charm to lock you for a bot-lane collapse"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are even and skill-based: Seraphine wants to poke with Q and zone your CS, but she has no hard lockdown yet, so respect her mana-efficient harass and farm safely without ever eating a free High Note. Trade only when her Q is on cooldown and you can tumble in for a clean auto reset.","mid":"From levels 4-6 Seraphine gets ahead: her E root and then Encore give her lane the CC to punish any greedy Vayne positioning, and paired with an enchanter or engage support she can chain a root into a kill. Play back, farm on the move, and don't contest anything until your first item is complete.","late":"Once your first item lands the matchup swings to you and only widens with 2+ items. Silver Bolts and your steroid-heavy DPS shred Seraphine's low health pool, she can't escape your repositioning, and you outscale her utility kit into a hard Vayne-favoured late game.","whys":["Level 1 is even because neither of you has a real trade tool yet and it's a skill CS lane.","Level 2 stays skill-based as Seraphine's Q poke is answered by your ability to farm on the move.","Level 3 is even since her root isn't reliably online yet and you can tumble her harass.","Levels 4-5 favour Seraphine because her Beat Drop root plus support engage out-threatens your all-in.","Level 6 favours Seraphine because Encore can charm-lock you for a bot-lane collapse.","First item favours Vayne because Silver Bolts melts her low base health once your DPS spike is online.","2+ items favour Vayne because you hyper-carry and she has no way to escape your kiting."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"sivir","win":["Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sivir's Boomerang Blade (Q) plus Ricochet (W) shove the wave and poke you off your CS, and her Spell Shield (E) eats your Condemn (E) if you throw it carelessly; farm on the move, never waste your E into a raised shield, and accept that she controls the lane tempo and pushes you under tower this early."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"On the Hunt (R) gives her whole bot lane a movement-speed burst to kite you or all-in with the support, and it's the peak of her lane pressure; you have no reliable way to punish it yet, so hold your ground under tower, dodge her Q, and don't get baited into a fight you can't win in the 2v2."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item is the turning point: with Silver Bolts (W) online and Sivir having zero self-peel besides one Spell Shield, you can bait the shield with a throwaway auto, then tumble in and start stacking your W procs faster than she can Ricochet you down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items deep Vayne hard-outscales Sivir; her kit is waveclear and utility, not dueling, so once you're the hyper-carry you kite her R burst, weave Q resets, and shred her in any extended fight while she can only shield one ability and run."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait Spell Shield with a cheap auto before committing Condemn","Reach first item where Silver Bolts outduels her waveclear kit","Drag the game to a 2+ item late where you hard-outscale her"],"foe":["Shove with Q and W to lock you under tower","Poke you off CS with Boomerang Blade","Use On the Hunt (R) speed to kite or all-in with support"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Sivir: her Boomerang Blade and Ricochet push the wave in and chunk you, and Spell Shield removes the value of your Condemn if you throw it on cooldown. Play for safe CS on the move, respect the shove, and take farm under tower rather than contesting a losing early trade.","mid":"Through levels 4-6 Sivir keeps the edge; her wave control plus On the Hunt let her lane dictate when to engage or disengage, and you still lack the item power to flip a 2v2. Farm patiently, dodge her Q poke, and don't force anything until your first completed item comes online.","late":"Your first item flips the lane and 2+ items make it a landslide. Silver Bolts and your escalating DPS overwhelm Sivir's low peel, your Q keeps you spaced through her R burst, and as a hyper-carry you dominate every extended fight into the late game.","whys":["Level 1 favours Sivir because her Q-W poke and shove control the lane from the start.","Level 2 favours Sivir as Ricochet and Boomerang push you off CS and chunk you.","Level 3 favours Sivir since her Spell Shield neutralizes your Condemn and she keeps shoving.","Levels 4-5 favour Sivir because her waveclear and lane tempo out-pressure your unspiked kit.","Level 6 favours Sivir because On the Hunt's team speed enables her all-in or kite.","First item favours Vayne because Silver Bolts and your DPS spike outduel her low-peel kit.","2+ items favour Vayne because you hard-outscale her utility kit as the hyper-carry."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"smolder","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Vayne","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Smolder is farming his Super Scorcher Breath (Q) stacks and pokes with Achewik Flare (W); the lane is even and skill-based, so deny his stacks by trading when his Q is on cooldown, tumble his W poke, and farm on the move without feeding him easy last-hits that accelerate his scaling."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Mobile Deathray (E) gives Smolder a repositioning dash plus a damage line, matching your tumble mobility, so his level 6 and yours roughly cancel; play the 2v2 cleanly, hold Condemn for when he dashes toward you, and treat this as a coin-flip skirmish window rather than a guaranteed win for either side."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item is your best swing: before Smolder's stacks fully come online, your Silver Bolts (W) and Q resets let you out-trade his mid-stack Q, so look to force an all-in with your support right as your first component completes and his DPS is still ramping."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game tightens back to even: fully-stacked Smolder's Q does execute-tier damage and his E gives him the mobility to kite you, so while you hyper-carry, he is one of the few scaling ADCs who keeps pace; win the spacing war with Q and Final Hour (R) rather than assuming a free outscale."}],"wants":{"you":["Force the fight at your first-item spike before his stacks mature","Deny Smolder's Q stacks by trading on his cooldowns","Win the spacing duel with Q resets and Final Hour"],"foe":["Stack Super Scorcher Breath (Q) toward the execute threshold","Poke safely with Achewik Flare (W) while farming","Kite with Mobile Deathray (E) to survive your all-ins"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a skill matchup: Smolder just wants to farm his Q stacks and poke with W, and you want to deny that scaling. Trade into his cooldowns, take CS on the move to avoid his poke, and keep the lane even without giving him free stacks that snowball his scaling.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stay even; Smolder's Mobile Deathray gives him the mobility to answer your tumble, so neither of you cleanly wins the 2v2 without support intervention. Play for measured trades, respect his E dash, and treat every skirmish as a coin flip decided by cooldowns and support CC.","late":"Your first-item window is the one clear Vayne-favoured beat, so force fights before his stacks mature; past that the late game rebalances to even, because a fully-stacked Smolder executes and his E kites your all-ins, keeping this a skill-decided spacing duel rather than a free outscale.","whys":["Level 1 is even as both of you farm and neither has a trading advantage yet.","Level 2 stays skill-based with Smolder poking and you denying while trading on cooldowns.","Level 3 is even since his Q stacks aren't mature and you can tumble his W poke.","Levels 4-5 are even because Mobile Deathray matches your tumble mobility in the 2v2.","Level 6 is skill-decided as both ults roughly cancel and fights hinge on cooldowns.","First item favours Vayne because your W and Q resets out-trade his still-ramping stacks.","2+ items is even because a fully-stacked Smolder executes and kites, keeping pace with your carry."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"swain","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Swain","Skill","Skill","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Bot-lane Swain leans on Nevermove (W) landing followed by Death's Hand (Q) bolts to chunk you, and once he hits his W-Q combo at level 4 he can zone you off CS; sidestep the delayed W root, farm on the move, and never stand in the open where his Q cone can hit you at max stacks."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Demonic Ascension (R) turns Swain into a durable drain tank in the 2v2, but it's healing and sustain, not lockdown, so your level 6 skirmish is a skill check; hold Condemn to interrupt his Nevermove setup and kite the ult's drain radius rather than trading blows inside it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item keeps the lane even-to-yours: Silver Bolts (W) shreds Swain's tanky drain-tank health bar percent-style, but his ult healing and W root mean you must land clean W procs from range; force fights only when his Nevermove is down so he can't root you into his combo."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, Vayne pulls clearly ahead: Swain is an immobile drain mage with one telegraphed root, and your Q spacing plus percent-health Silver Bolts let you kite outside his Nevermove range and melt him faster than his R can heal, making the late game firmly yours."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep Nevermove (W) so he can't root you into his combo","Use percent-health Silver Bolts to shred his tanky HP pool","Kite outside his root range into a Vayne-favoured late game"],"foe":["Land Nevermove (W) root to chain into Death's Hand","Zone you off CS with his Q-W combo at level 4","Drain-tank fights inside Demonic Ascension (R)"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a skill lane: Swain wants to land Nevermove and follow with Death's Hand, but before his combo comes fully online you can trade on even footing. Respect the delayed W root, farm on the move, and don't give him a free root that lets his Q cone stack damage on you.","mid":"Level 4 tips toward Swain as his W-Q combo and lane bulk let him zone you off CS, but level 6 pulls back to even because his ult is sustain rather than hard lockdown. Dodge Nevermove, hold Condemn to interrupt his setup, and skirmish only when his root is on cooldown.","late":"By 2+ items the lane is firmly Vayne-favoured. Swain is an immobile drain-tank with a single telegraphed root, and your percent-health Silver Bolts plus Q spacing let you kite outside Nevermove and shred him faster than Demonic Ascension can heal.","whys":["Level 1 is even as neither of you can commit a real trade before Swain's combo is online.","Level 2 stays skill-based with Swain poking and you farming on the move.","Level 3 is even since his Nevermove root isn't a reliable kill threat yet.","Levels 4-5 favour Swain because his W-Q combo zones you off CS with his lane bulk.","Level 6 is even because his ult is drain sustain, not lockdown, and you can kite it.","First item is skill-decided as Silver Bolts shreds his HP but his root and heal answer back.","2+ items favour Vayne because you kite outside his root and melt him past his ult healing."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"tristana","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tristana","Tristana","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early Tristana is farming with Explosive Charge (E) passive stacks and has short range before her passive scales, so levels 3-5 are an even skill lane; deny her free auto-attack stacks on you, tumble her Rocket Jump (W) if she dives in, and take clean CS on the move without letting her set up an E detonation."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Buster Shot (R) plus Rocket Jump gives Tristana a full all-in: she jumps on you, stacks Explosive Charge autos, and can knock you away from your support or into hers, so her level 6 out-threatens your solo skirmish; hold Condemn for her W landing and don't stand at detonation range without escape."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Tristana's first item pushes her ahead: her passive range plus a completed item let her stack E to full and burst you before your own DPS ramps, so respect her all-in range, keep minions between you, and avoid extended trades where her Explosive Charge can detonate on you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in the matchup flips to Vayne: once you're the hyper-carry your Silver Bolts (W) and Q resets out-DPS Tristana in a sustained fight, and while she has W-R mobility, you kite her jump, space with Condemn, and win the extended duel her burst kit can't sustain."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive her level 6-first-item all-in window with Condemn spacing","Deny Explosive Charge stacks by farming on the move","Reach 2 items where your sustained DPS beats her burst"],"foe":["Land Rocket Jump (W) to stack Explosive Charge autos","Combo Buster Shot (R) to displace you off your support","Spike on first item to burst you before your DPS ramps"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are an even skill lane: Tristana is short-range and stacking Explosive Charge, so you can farm on the move and deny her free auto stacks. Trade when her Rocket Jump is down, tumble her engage attempts, and keep the early game neutral without feeding her E detonations.","mid":"Level 6 and first item tip toward Tristana: Buster Shot plus Rocket Jump give her a full all-in, and her passive range with one item lets her burst you before your DPS ramps. Play back, hold Condemn for her W landing, keep minions between you, and avoid extended trades in her spike window.","late":"By 2+ items the lane flips firmly to Vayne. As the hyper-carry your Silver Bolts and Q resets out-DPS her burst in any sustained fight, you kite her Rocket Jump, and you space her out with Condemn to win the extended duel her kit can't sustain.","whys":["Level 1 is even as both farm and Tristana lacks her range spike or engage yet.","Level 2 stays skill-based with short-range Tristana unable to commit a strong trade.","Level 3 is even since you can deny her Explosive Charge stacks and tumble her jump.","Levels 4-5 are even as neither of you cleanly wins the 2v2 before her ult and item.","Level 6 favours Tristana because Buster Shot plus Rocket Jump give her a full all-in.","First item favours Tristana because her range and burst spike before your DPS ramps.","2+ items favour Vayne because your sustained hyper-carry DPS out-duels her burst kit."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"twitch","win":["Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Twitch abuses Ambush (Q) stealth to reposition and stack Deadly Venom, then Contaminate (E) detonates the poison for a burst that out-trades you early; ward the flanks so he can't roam onto you invisible, farm on the move, and never let your health drop into E-detonation range where he can chunk you from stealth."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Spray and Pray (R) turns Twitch into a piercing-auto lane bully who, paired with his support, can blow you up before your kit spikes; his level 6 all-in out-threatens yours, so respect the R timing, hold Condemn for when he emerges from Ambush, and don't contest fights where his poison stacks are already on you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item is where the lane finally levels off to a skill fight: with Silver Bolts (W) online you can trade back into Twitch's squishy body, but his Contaminate burst and R still make it a coin flip, so pick trades only when his E is down and his stealth is warded."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in it stays a skill matchup, not a free outscale: Twitch's Spray and Pray does absurd teamfight damage from stealth flanks, so while you hyper-carry, you must track his Ambush, space with Q and Final Hour, and win the positioning war rather than assuming you simply outduel him."}],"wants":{"you":["Ward flanks so Twitch can't Ambush onto you invisible","Trade back only when Contaminate (E) is on cooldown","Track his stealth and win the positioning war late"],"foe":["Stack Deadly Venom then detonate with Contaminate (E)","Use Ambush (Q) stealth to reposition and roam onto you","Bully lane and teamfights with Spray and Pray (R)"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 belong to Twitch: his Ambush stealth lets him reposition and stack Deadly Venom, and Contaminate detonates that poison for a burst that out-trades your early kit. Ward the flanks, farm on the move, keep your health out of E-detonation range, and don't contest a losing trade before you spike.","mid":"Level 6 keeps Twitch ahead; Spray and Pray plus his support make him a lane bully who can blow you up before your kit comes online. Respect his R and stealth timing, hold Condemn for when he emerges from Ambush, and play patiently for your first item rather than forcing a fight.","late":"First item onward the lane levels to a skill fight rather than a Vayne outscale. Silver Bolts lets you trade into his squishy body, but his Contaminate burst and stealth-flank Spray and Pray keep it even, so track his Ambush, space with Q and Final Hour, and win the positioning war.","whys":["Level 1 favours Twitch because his stealth and poison-detonate burst out-trade you early.","Level 2 favours Twitch as Ambush repositioning lets him stack and chunk you safely.","Level 3 favours Twitch since Contaminate detonation out-bursts your unspiked kit.","Levels 4-5 favour Twitch because his poison trades and roam threat control the lane.","Level 6 favours Twitch because Spray and Pray plus support make him a lane bully.","First item is skill-decided as Silver Bolts lets you trade but his burst keeps it even.","2+ items is skill-decided because his stealth-flank R damage matches your carry, hinging on positioning."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"varus","win":["Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Varus's window, not yours. His Piercing Arrow (Q) outranges everything you have and his Blighted Quiver (W) stacks melt you if you sit in three autos, so use Tumble (Q) purely to dodge his charged Q and reset your own auto, never to commit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Final Hour (R) is up but you're still behind: Varus can hold Chain of Corruption (R) as a hard peel, and if his support chains a follow-up you die before Silver Bolts (W) procs twice. Only look for a 6 all-in if he blew his ult or Q first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Kraken/Botrk timing is the pivot. Once you have a completed item plus the Vayne WR of ~55%, three-hit Silver Bolts shreds Varus's squishy frame and Condemn (E) into a wall ends any fight he starts with Q."},{"when":"Late","text":"Scaling is heavily yours. With Final Hour's invisibility on Tumble and true damage on W, you kite around his rooted Chain of Corruption and out-DPS his short-cooldown Q in extended 5v5 trades."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge charged Piercing Arrow with Tumble timing","Reach your first item power spike untaxed","Extended fights where three-hit W stacks land"],"foe":["Poke you off the wave with Q before lvl 6","Stack Blighted Quiver W then all-in early","End the lane before your item spike lands"]},"early":"Varus dominates levels 1-2: his auto range and Piercing Arrow poke you every time you step up to last-hit, so farm from max range behind your caster minions and only Tumble to secure CS or dodge a charged Q, never to trade.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Varus-favoured. His W blight stacks plus Q detonation chunk you if you commit, and his Chain of Corruption threatens a game-ending root, so respect his mana and only trade back when his Q is on cooldown.","late":"After your first item the lane flips hard toward you and the ~55% WR shows why: completed Silver Bolts true damage tears his low-HP frame, Condemn stops his engages, and Final Hour lets you win every extended teamfight duel.","whys":["Varus's superior auto range and Piercing Arrow poke own the level 1 last-hitting duel.","At level 2 his W blight and Q let him tax every CS attempt you make.","Level 3 gives Varus full poke-plus-blight combo pressure you can't answer yet.","Through levels 4-5 his sustained Q poke keeps you shoved and low.","At 6 his Chain of Corruption root plus support follow-up outkills your fresh Final Hour.","With one item Vayne's three-hit true damage finally overpowers Varus's squishy body.","In the 2+ item teamfight phase Vayne's kiting and true damage hard-outscale Varus."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Veigar","Veigar","Veigar","Veigar","Veigar","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"A bot-lane Veigar is a burst mage: his Baleful Strike (Q) poke and Dark Matter (W) zone punish you for stepping up to CS. Farm at range, use Tumble (Q) to sidestep Dark Matter's landing circle, and never walk into a spot where Event Horizon (E) can cage you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Primordial Burst (R) can nearly one-shot you if he lands Event Horizon first, and your fresh Final Hour (R) doesn't save you from being stunned and bursted. Only all-in when his E is on cooldown or your support has hard CC to peel his cage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you complete Kraken/Botrk the matchup swings: Vayne's ~52% WR reflects that three-hit Silver Bolts (W) plus Tumble mobility lets you close on his low-mobility body faster than he can re-cage you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is yours if you respect the cage. Final Hour invisibility on Tumble lets you dodge Event Horizon, and once inside his range his short frame melts to true damage before Primordial Burst comes back up."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep Dark Matter and Event Horizon with Tumble","Reach first item to threaten his squishy frame","Force him to waste Event Horizon before you commit"],"foe":["Poke you down with Baleful Strike stacks","Land Event Horizon into Primordial Burst combo","Zone you off farm with Dark Matter early"]},"early":"Veigar wins levels 1-2 by zoning: Baleful Strike out-ranges your autos and Dark Matter denies you safe CS, so last-hit from behind your minions and don't give him a free Q proc or a stack toward his infinite AP.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay his: Event Horizon into Dark Matter or Primordial Burst can delete you, so treat his cage as a death sentence, hold Condemn (E) to punish his flash, and only trade when his E is down.","late":"After one item and Final Hour online the lane flips to you and the ~52% WR follows: dodge the cage with Tumble, close the gap, and three-hit true damage shreds his low-HP mage frame in every skirmish.","whys":["Veigar's Baleful Strike range and Dark Matter zone control the level 1 farm.","At 2 his poke plus Dark Matter keep you off the wave and stacking his AP.","Level 3 gives Veigar the full cage-and-burst threat you can't yet survive.","Through 4-5 his Event Horizon into Primordial Burst can one-shot you.","At 6 his combo outdamages your fresh Final Hour if he lands the cage.","With a completed item Vayne's mobility and true damage overpower his squishy body.","In the 2+ item phase Vayne's kiting hard-outscales Veigar's single burst window."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Xayah out-trades you early: her Double Daggers (Q) poke and feather stacks let her win any prolonged exchange, and Bladecaller (E) recalls feathers to root you. Farm safe, use Tumble (Q) to dodge her feather line, and never sit in a trade long enough for her to recall a root."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Featherstorm (R) makes her untargetable and can dodge your Condemn (E) or a support's engage entirely, so a level 6 all-in often just wastes your Final Hour (R). Only commit if she has already used R or you can bait it before your support CCs."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first completed item is the flip: Vayne's true damage from three-hit Silver Bolts (W) outpaces her feather setup, and once you can survive her burst window the ~49% early gap starts closing in extended fights."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game you edge her in a pure duel: Final Hour invisibility on Tumble dodges her feathers and root, and true damage shreds her faster than she can stack Bladecaller, though her R still lets her escape bad commits."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge feather lines and Bladecaller roots with Tumble","Reach first item to survive her trade pattern","Bait Featherstorm before committing your all-in"],"foe":["Win early trades with Double Daggers and feathers","Land a Bladecaller root into support follow-up","Use Featherstorm to dodge your Condemn and engages"]},"early":"Xayah controls levels 1-2: her Q poke and feather stacks beat your short-range autos, so last-hit carefully behind minions and use Tumble only to dodge her Double Daggers, never to force a trade you'll lose.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Xayah-favoured because a recalled Bladecaller root plus her support can chain you down, and her clean waveclear denies your all-in windows, so respect the feather count and only step up when her E is spent.","late":"After your first item the lane tilts toward you and the sub-50 WR reflects how close it stays: true damage out-duels her feather setup, but her Featherstorm untargetability means you pick your fights and win the extended ones, not the coinflips.","whys":["Xayah's Double Daggers and feather stacks win the level 1 trade.","At 2 her poke and feather setup keep pressuring your CS.","Level 3 lets Xayah threaten a Bladecaller root into her support's follow-up.","Through 4-5 her feather stacking out-trades you in every extended exchange.","At 6 Featherstorm dodges your Condemn and blanks your fresh Final Hour all-in.","With one item Vayne's true damage finally out-duels Xayah's feather pattern.","In the 2+ item phase Vayne's kiting and true DPS edge out Xayah late."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Skill","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zeri kites you out early: her Burst Fire (Q) auto-poke pierces minions and her Ultrashock Laser (W) plus wall-dashing Spark Surge (E) let her hit you and leave before Silver Bolts (W) stacks. Farm at range, Tumble (Q) to dodge her W root line, and don't chase her over walls."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Lightning Crash (R) gives her huge move speed and AoE resets, so committing your Final Hour (R) into a fed Zeri usually just lets her dash away and re-engage on her terms. This phase is a skill check: punish only if she mispositions her E or eats your Condemn."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Around one completed item the lane levels out to a skill matchup: your true-damage three-hit answers her low base damage, but her mobility means whoever positions better and lands their key cooldown wins the trade."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game tips to you: Final Hour invisibility lets you stick through her Spark Surge dashes, and true damage from Silver Bolts shreds her squishy frame faster than her Q ramps, provided you dodge the Ultrashock root that sets up her burst."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Ultrashock Laser roots with Tumble timing","Reach late game where true damage out-shreds her","Punish mispositioned Spark Surge with Condemn"],"foe":["Kite you with Burst Fire pierce and Spark Surge dashes","Land Ultrashock Laser root into her support's CC","Snowball off Lightning Crash move speed and resets"]},"early":"Zeri owns levels 1-2 with her piercing Burst Fire auto-poke and constant Spark Surge repositioning, so you can't punish her; last-hit safely, use Tumble only to dodge her Ultrashock Laser, and never overextend chasing her mobility.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Zeri-favoured because her wall-dashing E and W root let her poke and disengage at will, and Lightning Crash amplifies that mobility, so hold Condemn as a punish and only trade when her E is on cooldown.","late":"By the first-item skill phase the lane evens out and then tips to you at 2+ items: true damage out-shreds her squishy body in extended fights, but her dash spam means the better-positioned player wins, so play for late scaling.","whys":["Zeri's piercing Burst Fire and Spark Surge mobility win the level 1 poke.","At 2 her auto-poke and dashes keep her safely ahead in trades.","Level 3 lets Zeri kite you with W root and wall-dashing E.","Through 4-5 her constant repositioning denies your all-in windows.","At 6 Lightning Crash mobility lets her dodge your Final Hour commit.","At one item the mobility-versus-true-damage trade becomes an even skill check.","In the 2+ item phase Vayne's true damage hard-outscales Zeri's squishy frame."]},
  {"a":"vayne_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Ziggs","Ziggs","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"The early lane is a positioning skill check: Ziggs's Bouncing Bomb (Q) poke and Satchel Charge (W) zone deny you free step-ups, but he has no way to kill you if you dodge. Weave last-hits between his Q bounces, Tumble (Q) to break the bomb's path, and stay off his Hexplosive Minefield (E) tiles."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Around 4-6 Ziggs pulls ahead: Satchel Charge can knock you out of all-in range and his poke plus Mega Inferno Bomb (R) chunk you before you close. Your fresh Final Hour (R) doesn't beat his disengage, so only commit when W is down and your support has hard CC."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first completed item flips it and the ~55% WR shows why: once Kraken/Botrk is online, three-hit Silver Bolts (W) plus Tumble closes the gap his Satchel can't fully deny, and his squishy frame melts once you're on him."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is firmly yours: Final Hour invisibility on Tumble dodges his Q line and Mega Inferno Bomb, and true damage shreds him in seconds once you slip past his zoning in a teamfight."}],"wants":{"you":["Weave last-hits between Bouncing Bomb pokes","Reach first item to gap-close past his zoning","Force Satchel Charge before your all-in"],"foe":["Poke you off the wave with Bouncing Bomb","Use Satchel Charge to deny your all-in range","Zone your CS with Hexplosive Minefield tiles"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even skill matchup: Ziggs pokes with Bouncing Bomb but can't threaten a kill, so it comes down to your dodging, last-hitting cleanly behind minions and using Tumble to sidestep his Q bounces without wasting it.","mid":"Levels 4-6 tilt to Ziggs as his Satchel Charge disengage and stacked poke plus Mega Inferno Bomb keep you out of all-in range, so respect his zoning, hold Condemn (E), and only commit when his W is on cooldown.","late":"After your first item the lane swings hard to you and the ~55% WR follows: true damage from three-hit Silver Bolts shreds his squishy body, Final Hour lets you slip his zoning, and you out-duel him in every extended fight.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill check since Ziggs pokes but can't kill you.","At 2 it stays skill-based, decided by whether you dodge his Bouncing Bomb.","Level 3 remains even as neither of you can commit a kill through the poke.","At 4-5 Ziggs's Satchel disengage and stacked poke deny your all-in range.","At 6 his Mega Inferno Bomb and W disengage beat your fresh Final Hour.","With one item Vayne's true damage and mobility overpower his squishy zoning.","In the 2+ item phase Vayne's kiting hard-outscales Ziggs's single poke pattern."]}
